My meme

Feeling of learning different computer language

This meme is created base on one of the illustrator personal image / appearance sticker and one of the popular meme style

For most of the compsci students, R maybe the most user friendly computer language and the upcoming one for them will be python. After they finished the basic python course in stage 1, they will start learning java which will force them to rebuild their knowledge in programming language. Later, they will be introduced one of the most old-school and difficult computer language C and C++, which is a higher level language and is much more easy to get error language

#read the library 
library(magick)

#call the image
image_1 <- image_read("necho_7.jpg") %>% image_scale(500)
image_2 <- image_read("necho_2.jpg") %>% image_scale(500)
image_3 <- image_read("necho_3.jpg") %>% image_scale(500)
image_4 <- image_read("necho_4.jpg") %>% image_scale(500)
image_5 <- image_read("necho_5.jpg") %>% image_scale(500)

#set up different size blank space for text
space_1 <- image_blank(width=500, height=500,color="#808080")
space_2 <- image_blank(width=500, height=553,color="#808080")
space_3 <- image_blank(width=500, height=571,color="#808080")

###they are not in order ####

#chunk 1
chunk_1 <- image_annotate(space_2,text = "Java Script",
                          color = "#ffffff",
                          size = 90, 
                          font = "Impact",
                          gravity = "center")

#chunk 2
chunk_2 <- image_annotate(space_1,text = "Java",
                          color = "#ffffff",
                          size = 90, 
                          font = "Impact",
                          gravity = "center")

#chunk 3
chunk_3 <- image_annotate(space_1,text = "C and C++",
                          color = "#ffffff",
                          size = 90, 
                          font = "Impact",
                          gravity = "center")

#chunk 4
chunk_4 <- image_annotate(space_1,text = "python",
                          color = "#ffffff",
                          size = 90, 
                          font = "Impact",
                          gravity = "center")

#chunk 5
chunk_5 <- image_annotate(space_3,text = "R",
                          color = "#ffffff",
                          size = 90, 
                          font = "Impact",
                          gravity = "center")

#combine the image and text into one component 
level_1 <- image_append(c(image_1,chunk_1))

level_2 <- image_append(c(image_2,chunk_2))

level_3 <- image_append(c(image_3,chunk_3))

level_4 <- image_append(c(image_4,chunk_4))

level_5 <- image_append(c(image_5,chunk_5))

#combine all component into one vector
test <- c(level_5,level_4,level_2,level_1,level_3)

# turn the vector into one image
meme <- image_append(test,stack = TRUE)

#save the image to drive 
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

#call the image to perview
meme

My animated GIF

The feeling of lecturer to coderunner on the first two weeks

POV of the compsci lecturer for this semester in the first 2 week. This gif / meme is created base on one of the illustrator personal image / appearance gif stickers. I have collected all the images used for the sticker and turned them into jpg file. The rest of the images are collected from one of piazza replay from lecturer at the start of the semester, and the error image is collected when the coderunner crashed.

For the animation, I add some content base on what happen on coderunner during the first two weeks of the semester by adding text with annotate function and creating different version of the sticker.

#set up the blank space for image add note
space_bg <- image_blank(width=290, height=320,color="#000000")

#set up image add note 
d1 <- image_annotate(space_bg,"Update coderunner to \nnewest java version",size = 30,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact',gravity = "center")
w2 <- image_annotate(space_bg,"Second week \nafter update",size = 30,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact',gravity = "center")
cr <- image_annotate(space_bg,"Coderunner",size = 30,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact',gravity = "center")

#combine the background (image blank) with image above to place image center
bug <- image_composite(space_bg,image_scale(image_read("bug.jpg"),290),offset = "+0+150")

#call the image for apart of the animation 
crash_1 <- image_scale(image_read("crash-1.jpg"),290)
crash_2 <- image_scale(image_read("crash-2.jpg"),290)
crash_3 <- image_scale(image_read("crash-3.jpg"),290)

#turn the part above into animation
crash <- image_animate(c(cr,crash_1,crash_2,crash_3),fps = 1)

#turn image add note into animation 
space_d1 <- image_animate(c(d1,cr,bug,bug),fps = 1)
space_w2 <- image_animate(w2,fps = 1)

#call the image for another part of the animation
necho_1 <- image_read("necho-1.gif")
necho_2 <- image_read("necho-2.gif")
necho_3 <- image_read("necho-3.gif")
necho_4 <- image_read("necho-4.gif")

#call out two different version of one image for animation
java1 <- image_background(image_scale(image_read("java.jpg"),30),"#D9F9F9")
java2 <- image_scale(image_read("java.jpg"),30)

#version 1 image
necho_java1 <- image_composite(necho_1,image_rotate(java1,225),offset = "+50+100")
necho_java2 <- image_composite(necho_2,image_rotate(java1,225),offset = "+50+175")
necho_java3 <- image_composite(necho_3,image_rotate(java1,225),offset = "+50+100")
necho_java4 <- image_composite(necho_4,image_rotate(java1,225),offset = "+50+175")

#version 2 image
necho_java1_b <- image_composite(necho_1,image_rotate(java2,225),offset = "+50+100")
necho_java2_b <- image_composite(necho_2,image_rotate(java2,225),offset = "+50+175")
necho_java3_b <- image_composite(necho_3,image_rotate(java2,225),offset = "+50+100")
necho_java4_b <- image_composite(necho_4,image_rotate(java2,225),offset = "+50+175")

#first chunk of the animation 
add <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"First day after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
         image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2, 'Add'),"First day after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
         image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3, 'Add'),"First day after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
         image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"First day after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#000000",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 10)

#second chunk of the animation
modu <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"Two week after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
          image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2_b, 'Modulate'),"Two week after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
          image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3_b, 'Modulate'),"Two week after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
          image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"Two week after \ninstall java",size = 21,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 25)

#another version of first chunk 
add_lang <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"learning \npython",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
              image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2, 'Add'),"learning \npython",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
              image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3, 'Add'),"learning \npython",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
              image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"learning \npython",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 10)

#another version of the second chunk 
modu_lang <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"learning \njava",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2_b, 'Modulate'),"learning \njava",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3_b, 'Modulate'),"learning \njava",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"learning \njava",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 25)

#first of the animation 
necho_punch <- c(add,add,add,modu,modu,modu,modu,modu,modu,modu)

#second version of the animation
lang <- c(add_lang,add_lang,add_lang,modu_lang,modu_lang,modu_lang,modu_lang)

#first chunk of the final version animation
add_cr <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2, 'Add'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3, 'Add'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact'),
               image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1, 'Add'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#000000",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 10)

#second chunk of the final version animation 
modu_cr <- c(image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
             image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java2_b, 'Modulate'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
             image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java3_b, 'Modulate'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact'),
             image_annotate(image_flatten(necho_java1_b, 'Modulate'),"Lecturer:",size = 25,color = "#ffffff",font ='Impact')) %>% image_animate(fps = 50)

#combine all the chunk together 
coderunner <- c(space_d1,add_cr,add_cr,add_cr,space_w2,crash,modu_cr,modu_cr,modu_cr,modu_cr,modu_cr,modu_cr)

coderunner
